[
    {
        "content": "<p>So arguably, this is just me not knowing how to write good roc/pipeline enough, but one thing I find annoying in Roc is when I have to add an extra function and it requires a set of parenthesis.</p>\n<p>A common example is when with integer size mismatches. Here is an over extreme example of what I mean:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Oh wait, x is a U64, not a Nat:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nx\">out</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Oh wait, I actually want to shift y like an I64, not a U64:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Hmm... That line looks gross, let's split it up:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">x = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">y = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">out = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Oh wait, I can't shadow x and y in roc:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">x1 = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">y1 = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">out = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"nx\">x1</span> <span class=\"nx\">y1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This of course gets worse as lines get longer and the parenthesis start to really add up.</p>\n<p>Also, it is kinda annoying to need to go x1 x2 x3 if I have to modify a value multiple times. I think it makes some code much harder to read. Maybe that is some form of mutation bias. This pushes me to want more on the same line, but that leads back to the tons of parenthesis problem</p>\n<p>I think always using the same name is also really useful to ensure that you will always enable the roc compiler to optimize to not have copies. If I only ever have access to the newest version of a variable, I can't accidentally reference an old versions.</p>\n<p>Anyway, I don't really have a direct solution or idea, I have seen differing solutions like <code>$</code> in haskell or just shadowing in general like you would see in rust.</p>\n<p>Overall wondering what peoples thoughts are/how this could be better. Might just need to change how I write code.</p>",
        "id": 276089995,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1647885266
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My hunch is that editor will solve your problems :)</p>",
        "id": 276092492,
        "sender_full_name": "Zeljko Nesic",
        "timestamp": 1647886391
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/parenthesis.20and.20naming/near/276089995\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out = </span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>thoughts on this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out =</span>\n    <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span> <span class=\"nx\">x</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276095331,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1647887549
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(personally that's how I'd write it!)</p>",
        "id": 276095436,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1647887591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if <code>x</code> had a longer name, I'd probably go one step further:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out =</span>\n    <span class=\"nx\">x</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">y</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but I generally think it looks kinda weird when a super short variable name is alone at the beginning of a pipe <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 276095647,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1647887656
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">out =</span>\n    <span class=\"nx\">something</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toNat</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">shiftRightBy</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toI64</span> <span class=\"nx\">somethingElse</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span> <span class=\"nx\">Num</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">toU64</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276095727,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1647887689
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok. So a lot of pipelining. That will definitely take my brain to some getting used to. Definitely more readable.</p>\n<p>Out of curiosity, what would you do with something like this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">t0 = </span> <span class=\"nx\">someCalculation</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">t1 =</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"nx\">t0</span> <span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span> <span class=\"k\">then</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t0</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">else</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t0</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">t2 =</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"nx\">t1</span> <span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span> <span class=\"k\">then</span>\n       <span class=\"nx\">modWithNonzero</span> <span class=\"nx\">t1</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">else</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t1</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># use t2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Can the repeated version naming be made better?</p>",
        "id": 276098521,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1647888976
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At least in other languages, I tend to just give sub-expressions their own names on separate lines</p>",
        "id": 276098526,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1647888978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel pipelines are better suited to single-value transformations (rather than binary operations, which feel unbalanced to me when using pipelines)</p>",
        "id": 276098826,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1647889137
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree, but then you have to name the sub-expressions which is part of the problem I have.</p>",
        "id": 276099000,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1647889217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In some functions there will be a lot of these.</p>",
        "id": 276099111,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1647889261
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sometimes it works out to decompose those into smaller functions, but not always</p>",
        "id": 276101809,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1647890695
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I go out of my way to give subexpressions names that are \"whatever I would put in a comment\", or some reason why I'm doing the operation. Sometimes that ends up being really low-level like <code>limited</code> or <code>rounded</code> or something but reasons <em>why</em> are better names. I think it's valuable for debuggability / readability.</p>",
        "id": 276102598,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Carroll",
        "timestamp": 1647891164
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I mean, obviously that's how to name things! The point is I still like to do that even for small things like this because it helps me think through it and understand my own code.</p>",
        "id": 276103356,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Carroll",
        "timestamp": 1647891579
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/parenthesis.20and.20naming/near/276098521\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Out of curiosity, what would you do with something like this?</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">t0 = </span> <span class=\"nx\">someCalculation</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">t1 =</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"nx\">t0</span> <span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span> <span class=\"k\">then</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t0</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">else</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t0</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">t2 =</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"nx\">t1</span> <span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span> <span class=\"k\">then</span>\n       <span class=\"nx\">modWithNonzero</span> <span class=\"nx\">t1</span> <span class=\"nx\">range</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">else</span>\n        <span class=\"nx\">t1</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># use t2</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>for this one I might extract a helper function:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">ensureBelow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">minimum</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">transform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">minimum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">then</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">transform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">minimum</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">else</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"nf\">someCalculation</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ensureBelow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">range</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sub</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ensureBelow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">range</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">modWithNonzero</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276110804,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1647895536
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd assume this would end up inlining to the original</p>",
